HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1571
By Travis
A RESOLUTION to celebrate the birth of August Jett Cates.
WHEREAS, we take great pleasure in celebrating the births of our State's newest
citizens; and
WHEREAS, August Jett Cates recently made his grand entrance into the world at 1:40
a.m. on Sunday, April 12, 2026, weighing 8.3 pounds; and
WHEREAS, his arrival brought great pride and joy to his family, including his parents,
Rachel Cates and Krys Cates; his sister, Hadley Jane Cates; his grandparents, Representative
Ron Travis and Laura Travis; his aunt, Jessica Shannon; and his cousins, Alley Jo Shannon,
Beckham Colby Shannon, and Finley Scout Shannon; and
WHEREAS, the Cateses are highly respected members of their community; they are the
very epitome of good neighbors, as they always endeavor to treat others as they would like to
be treated; and
WHEREAS, for nine months, they eagerly anticipated the birth of their precious baby boy
and worked assiduously to prepare for his entrance into the world; and
WHEREAS, this wonderful new arrival is certain to bring joy and excitement to the hearts
of family and friends alike; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to join the proud new parents, friends, and relatives of
August Jett Cates upon the celebration of such a joyous milestone in their lives; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we celebrate the arrival of August Jett Cates and wish Rachel and Krys
Cates and family all the best in their adventures with their little boy.
